cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language generation (NLG) in spoken dialogue systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses various machine learning architectures used for NLG, such as sequence-to-sequence models (cs.AI) and the evaluation of these systems (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of grammatical rules and templates for NLG (cs.SD) and the potential for reducing the need for data annotation (cs.NE).
